text: Interestingly, previous studies revealed that the pattern of cytokines expression after infection with prototype subtype 3 strain Lena differed compared to subtype 1 strains [16, 17] . Together with observations from a study on another subtype 3 strain SU1-bel [11] , where greater interferon-Î³ response was noted, those results suggested that observed higher pathogenicity may be a result of enhanced inflammatory immune response.
